During a press conference at the G7 summit in France, President Trump and Chancellor Merkel discussed various topics, including trade, military, defense, and the fight against ISIS. They expressed optimism about reaching a trade deal and preventing Iran from obtaining nuclear weapons. President Trump also mentioned the ongoing trade negotiations with China and the possibility of hosting the next G7 summit at his golf course in Miami. Chancellor Merkel addressed the issue of Russia and expressed the need for progress on the Minsk Agreement. They both discussed the importance of promoting female leaders and gender equality initiatives. President Trump mentioned that he has been invited to visit Berlin and expressed his interest in accepting the invitation.